{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"160057af-a440-4d2c-9082-1fdb51a82b37","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Unsupported Target Frameworks**\n\nMSTest v3 drops support for end-of-life runtimes. Two of your three targets are affected:\n\n| Framework | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported (.NET Framework ≥ 4.6.2) |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (minimum is `net6.0`) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (minimum is `net6.0`) |\n\nYou'll need to update those TFMs — e.g., `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or later) and `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0` (or later).\n\n**Package Consolidation**\n\nMSTest v3 replaces the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages with a single **`MSTest`** meta-package. Your migration would look like:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove both old packages, replace with: -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n```\n\n**Other Notable Breaking Changes**\n\n- Some previously deprecated APIs are removed.\n- Default behavior changes (e.g., test class/method lifecycle attributes are stricter).\n\nWould you like me to update the `.csproj` for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ac8fa437-432f-4023-a98e-e2cc7a344446","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nKey compatibility issues with MSTest v3:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 drops support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's out of support from Microsoft anyway)\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` is no longer supported\n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` (`net462`) — I need to check. MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+, so this should be fine actually. Wait, let me think again. MSTest v3 (3.x) minimum supported frameworks are:\n   - .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n   - .NET 6.0+\n   \n   So `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` would be problematic.\n\n2. **Package consolidation**: MSTest v3 consolidates `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` into a single `MSTest` package (or `MSTest.TestFramework` v3).\n\nThe core issue is that MSTest v3 requires .NET 6.0 or later for .NET Core projects, which means the `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` targets won't be compatible with the new version.","outputTokens":812,"requestId":"481D:1C33BD:6300489:6B4DFE1:69FBFCE7"},"id":"375e4ca5-d9be-4c61-bff0-bfc9b4a1b4f6","timestamp":"2026-05-07T02:46:14.882Z","parentId":"3054f7ef-cb99-4825-b3c9-c1cd6032f36d"}
